Class AbstractPartyProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractPartyProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, IParty
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PartyProxy

    public abstract class AbstractPartyProxy
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
implements IParty

    A data-access layer data-transfer object (DTO) lazy-loading proxy for the Party. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    An abstract entity that is either a person or an organization

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
